An 18-year-old man was “seriously assaulted” yesterday evening, on April 23. Kent Police are now “combing” parts of the centre to find the attacker, according to reports. The incident occurred between 8.45pm and 8.55pm near the junction with Station Road. The victim’s injuries were “consistent with stab wounds”, Kent Police reported. Officers arrived at the scene along with South East Coast Ambulance Service. After the man’s conditions were examined, he was taken to a London hospital. One, quoted in KentOnline, said: “What is happening to Maidstone? It used to be such a quiet place, but it’s constant trouble now.” Another added: “This side of town is frightening now, there seems to be something going wrong every weekend. “It’s the part of town you want to avoid now.” READ MORE: Panicked Putin launches frenzied 'salvage mission' to bury secrets This remained in place this morning, on April 24. Four police officers were guardian the area while six forensic officers searched for evidence, according to KentOnline. They said: “Witnesses are being urged to come forward following a serious assault in Maidstone… “An investigation into the incident is ongoing and officers are appealing to anyone who witnessed what happened or who has any information to call Kent Police on 01622 604100.” DON'T MISS:Boris urged to cut the ‘soundbites’ and focus on action [OPINION]Tory civil war erupts as Scottish Conservatives REFUSE to back Boris [REPORT]Prince Andrew legal settlement with Giuffre 'will have been millions' [REVEAL] Alternatively, witnesses can contact Crimestoppers anonymously. This can be done either by calling 0800 555111 or using the anonymous online form.